</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1425,1989]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1893,1917]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,474,1894,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvipenis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,474,1894,1917]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">J. curvipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[484,578,1893,1917]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[484,578,1893,1917]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang" authorityName="Zhang" box="[711,929,1893,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis box="[711,847,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">J. lamellata</emphasis>
Zhang
</taxonomicName>
externally and also has rather similar male pygofer. However, it differs in the structure of the aedeagal shaft which is slender, cylindrical and strongly recurved at base; in 
<taxonomicName box="[271,403,1965,1989]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis box="[271,403,1965,1989]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">J. lamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shaft has lateral lamellate processes and is slightly curved anteriorly in the distal region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
